Events.BriefDescription: Cache Lookups: Read Requests and Read Prefetches
Events.PublicDescription: Counts the number of times the LLC was accessed - this includes code, data, prefetches and hints coming from L2.  This has numerous filters available.  Note the non-standard filtering equation.  This event will count requests that lookup the cache multiple times with multiple increments.  One must ALWAYS set umask bit 0 and select a state or states to match.  Otherwise, the event will count nothing.   CHAFilter0[24:21,17] bits correspond to [FMESI] state. Read transactions

Events.BriefDescription: DRAM Activate Count : Read transaction on Page Empty or Page Miss : Counts the number of DRAM Activate commands sent on this channel.  Activate commands are issued to open up a page on the DRAM devices so that it can be read or written to with a CAS.  One can calculate the number of Page Misses by subtracting the number of Page Miss precharges from the number of Activates.
Events.PublicDescription: DRAM Activate Count : Read transaction on Page Empty or Page Miss

Events.BriefDescription: DRAM Activate Count : Write transaction on Page Empty or Page Miss : Counts the number of DRAM Activate commands sent on this channel. Events.BriefDescription: Read Pending Queue Allocations : Counts the number of allocations into the Read Pending Queue.  This queue is used to schedule reads out to the memory controller and to track the requests.  Requests allocate into the RPQ soon after they enter the memory controller, and need credits for an entry in this buffer before being sent from the HA to the iMC.  They deallocate after the CAS command has been issued to memory.  This includes both ISOCH and non-ISOCH requests.
Events.PublicDescription: Read Pending Queue Allocations
